@node POPMISC_CONSTRUCTOR "popmisc_plugin: Constructors / Destructor"

   @{BG shine}Constructor@{BG back}

      @{b}popmisc(@{"tags" link POPMISC_TAGS}=NIL:PTR TO tagitem)@{ub}

      For creating a new plugin object use for example:
      @{FG fill}
      DEF popmisc:PTR TO popmisc_plugin
      NEW popmisc.popmisc([..., TAG_DONE])
      @{FG text}

@endnode

@node POPMISC_METHODS "popmisc_plugin: New Methods"

   @{b}set(@{"tag" link POPMISC_TAGS}, value)@{ub}

      By calling this method it's possible to change attributes
      at runtime. You can use all tags with the S flag set.
      This method can also be used before the GUI is created and when
      the window is closed.
      Value is a LONG and contains the argument for the used tag.
      @{FG fill}
      Example:
      DEF popmisc:PTR TO popmisc_plugin
      ...
      NEW popmisc.popmisc([..., TAG_DONE])
      ...
      popmisc.set(PLA_PopMisc_Disabled, TRUE)
      ...
      @{FG text}

   @{b}value,check:=get(@{"tag" link POPMISC_TAGS})@{ub}

      This method is the counterpart to set. All tags with G flag
      can be used. Argument is the tag you want to get. Return values
      are the requested value and as second a boolean value. So if
      check is FALSE the used tag can't be get.

      @{FG fill}...
      value,check:=popmisc.get(PLA_PopMisc_Disabled)
      ...@{FG text}

      After this:
       value=TRUE
       check=TRUE

      But if you try:

      @{FG fill}...
      value,check:=popmisc.get(PLA_PopMisc_ListViewX)
      ...@{FG text}

      Then you get this:
       value:=-1
       check:=FALSE

@endnode

@node POPMISC_TAGS "popmisc_plugin: Tags"

 The letters [ISG] show when the tags can be used.
 I = @{"Initalisation" link POPMISC_CONSTRUCTOR}
 S = @{"Set Method" link POPMISC_METHODS}
 G = @{"Get Method" link POPMISC_METHODS 18}


    @{FG shine}PLA_PopMisc_ButtonText@{FG text}             [ISG]

        The initial contents of the button the
        user presses to bring up the listview;
        defaults to an appropriate string for
        the PLUGIN's @{FG shine}PLA_PopMisc_ListType@{FG text}.

    @{FG shine}PLA_PopMisc_StringText@{FG text}             [ISG]

        The initial contents of the string gadget
        which will be modified by the actions of
        the user.

    @{FG shine}PLA_PopMisc_CaseSensitive@{FG text}          [ISG]

        Boolean; the list is sorted alphabetically,
        and if this tag is TRUE then it will be sorted
        according to case as well.

    @{FG shine}PLA_PopMisc_RemoveDuplicates@{FG text}       [ISG]

        Boolean; whether or nor entities with the
        same name should appear more than once in the
        list.

    @{FG shine}PLA_PopMisc_ListType@{FG text}               [I..]

        Which type of system entity popmisc_plugin
        should display in its list.

        Can be one of six values:

            PLV_PopMisc_DevicesList
            PLV_PopMisc_LibrariesList
            PLV_PopMisc_MemNodesList
            PLV_PopMisc_PortsList
            PLV_PopMisc_ResourcesList
            PLV_PopMisc_TasksList (default)

    @{FG shine}PLA_PopMisc_ListViewX@{FG text}              [I..]
  & @{FG shine}PLA_PopMisc_ListViewY@{FG text}              [I..]

        These two values will be passed through as
        DCLV_RELX and DCLV_RELY to the instance of
        @{b}dclistview_plugin@{ub} used to create the
        listview. (See @{"dclistview.doc" link dclistview.doc/MAIN} for more
        information.)

    @{FG shine}PLA_PopMisc_Disabled@{FG text}               [ISG]

        Disable or enable the PLUGIN. Setting this
        tag causes the PLUGIN to become disabled;
        it gets a ghost pattern.

@endnode

@node POPMISC_EXCEPTIONS "popmisc_plugin: Exceptions"

   @{BG shine}Constructor@{BG back}

    "util" will be raised if the utility.library has not
    been opened.

    "baty" will be raised if the usr has set an illegal
    @{FG shine}PLA_PopMisc_ListType@{FG text} value.

@endnode

